ional identity for Russia. In this eye-opening and evocative book, John Burgess examines Russian Orthodoxy's resurgence from a grassroots level, providing Western readers with an enlightening, inside look at the new Russia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aChristianity and culturexHistoryy21st century. 0aChurch renewalxRusskai͡a pravoslavnai͡a t͡serkov'xHistoryy21stcentury. 0aNational characteristics, RussianxHistoryy21st century. 0aNationalismxReligious aspectsxRusskai͡a pravoslavnai͡at͡serkovʹ. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300227635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300227635.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles